post_text: Put your artistic skills to the test before the start of school and submit your sidewalk chalk art to @cityofsantaclara to win some Santa Clara swag!
shared_text:
City of Santa Clara
August 11 at 10:41 PM ·

SIDEWALK CHALK ART CONTEST! 🎨 Get outside and create your own chalk art masterpiece and WIN your very own Teddy! 🧸😷 Create chalk art with the theme, "Summer 2020 Santa Clara". Show us you #LoveSantaClara!

➡️ Email photos of your chalk art by Monday, Aug. 17 to: PRCustomerServe@SantaClaraCA.gov
➡️ Include name, age, category and (2) photos of artwork.
➡️ The community will vote for their favorites and winners will receive Teddy and more Santa Clara swag!

Category A: Age 5 and under
Category B: 12 years and younger
Category C: 13 – 18 years
Category D: 19 years and older

More details at SantaClaraCA.gov/VirtualParksandRec
#SantaClaraHasItCovered

Assemblymember Kansen Chu is sharing a COVID-19 Update.
July 14 at 9:13 PM ·

Please share! I'm hosting a free mask and hand sanitizer distribution. Stop by my District Office (parking lot) on Friday, July 17 from 4pm to 6pm to get 10 masks and 2 hand sanitizers per household. https://bit.ly/2CnWjBf

¡Por favor comparte! Estoy organizando una distribución gratuita de máscara y desinfectante para manos. Pase por mi Oficina de Distrito (estacionamiento) el Viernes 17 de Julio de 4pm a 6pm para obtener 10 máscaras y 2 desinfectantes para manos por hogar. https://bit.ly/2CnWjBf

"As we finish up our last week of the 2019-2020 school year, this is my last weekly message while we break for summer. I want to take a moment to express my gratitude to our students, families, and staff for your patience, grace, and dedication to persevere through these last 10 weeks with us. It hasn’t been easy — there have been many transitions for everyone along the way — but we rose to the challenge together as one community. We can all be proud. Now is the time for some rest… time to recharge and regroup. Please have a good summer and stay well." -- Superintendent Kemp
https://bit.ly/2UlHl4F

California School Employees Association (CSEA)
May 19, 2014 at 3:00 PM ·

Happy Classified School Employee Week! This week, school districts throughout California will celebrate the essential roles classified employees play in the lives of students, in support of district staff and faculty, and in public education as a whole.

CSEA members provide a multitude of essential services to create a nurturing environment for learning at California public schools. Comment below with your job title and let's celebrate how much we do every day to support and inspire California's students.
text:
Join us in celebrating our amazing classified employees during Classified School Employee Week!

May 19, 2014 at 3:00 PM ·

Happy Classified School Employee Week! This week, school districts throughout California will celebrate the essential roles classified employees play in the lives of students, in support of district staff and faculty, and in public education as a whole.

CSEA members provide a multitude of essential services to create a nurturing environment for learning at California public schools. Comment below with your job title and let's celebrate how much we do every day to support and inspire California's students.

post_text:
Shout out to our AMAZING teachers, support staff, administrators, students, and families for being so incredibly flexible and supportive as we mobilized in record time to re-instate learning for our children. When a three week shelter-in-place by our county turned into an indefinite one by the state, we knew we had to alter course. Together, we completely flipped learning from a hundreds-year-old traditional in-person learning model to virtual distance learning in less than a week. We are #SCUSDproud of everyone and you all are getting much deserved recognition!

https://www.sfchronicle.com/bayarea/article/Districts-inconsistent-on-distance-learning-15157557.php @sfchronicle

Here’s how the College Board is supporting students and schools during this time:

1️⃣ Free, live and on-demand AP courses. Lessons will begin March 25.

2️⃣ A new at-home testing option. Students will be able to test on a computer, tablet, or smartphone.

“During this challenging time, we will work to give every AP student the opportunity to earn the college credit and placement they’ve been working toward all year while maintaining a focus on the health and safety of our AP community.”

More details here: http://spr.ly/61851tbn3.
shared_text:
The College Board
March 20 at 5:24 PM ·

We know the coronavirus has created challenges for AP students and teachers. Here’s how the College Board will support you during this time:

1️⃣ We’re providing free, live and on-demand AP courses

To support AP students affected by school closures due to COVID-19, students and schools will have access to live AP review lessons, delivered by AP teachers from across the country. Lessons will begin March 25.

2️⃣ We’re developing a new at-home testing option

Because of the challenges created by COVID-19, we’re developing a new at-home AP Exam option. Students will be able to test on a computer, tablet, or smartphone.

We will invest so that every AP student impacted by COVID-19 has the tools and connectivity they need to review AP content online and take the exam from home.

During this challenging time, we will work to give every AP student the opportunity to earn the college credit and placement they’ve been working toward all year while maintaining a focus on the health and safety of our AP community.

More details here: http://spr.ly/61851tbn3.
